Description: Small false door of Ranefer: the lintel and drum of this diminutive false door are inscribed with the name and titles of Ranefer in fair, sunk relief. No colour remains.
Curator's comments: Bibliography. The British Museum, 'A guide to the Egyptian galleries (Sculpture)' (London, 1909), p. 27.
Bibliographic references: James 1961 / Hieroglyphic texts from Egyptian stelae, etc. Part 1 (pl.20)
